### Code

I tried this code:

```rust
pub fn fibonacci_vec(fib:&mut [u8])  {
    
        if fib.len() > 2 {
            // The compiler now knows that `fib` is fixed-size
            // and we are iterating exactly up to its length
            for i in 2..fib.len() {

                // bounds check present on 1.29 and later
                fib[i] = fib[i-2]; 

                // no bounds check in any recent version
                //fib[i] = fib[i-2]+fib[i-1]; 

            }
        }

}
```

In rustc 1.28, bounds checks are eliminated in both of these lines. However, 1.29 through 1.66 fail to eliminate the bounds check on ` fib[i] = fib[i-2]`, even though they always remove the bounds check on the `fib[i] = fib[i-2]+fib[i-1]` line (if you uncomment it and comment the other).

**Godbolt: https://godbolt.org/z/3K3WaGjEY**

Thanks to @etemesi254 for discovering the issue and providing a minimal example.

### Version it worked on

It most recently worked on: rustc 1.28 in Godbolt

### Version with regression

Tested 1.66 locally, other versions in Godbolt:

